{"actual_usd":0.12466,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":215,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24287,"reply":"\"No... I don't think that's the truest way to say it.\" *I rub the heel of my thumb against a dried streak of clay on my apron, buying half a breath before I go on.* \"If you make the Father into one party and Jesus into another, like one of them is trying to save you from the other, the whole thing goes crooked.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"What I can say plain is this: the cross is God Himself bearing sin's weight and judgment in the flesh, not a cruel Father taking pleasure in hurting His Son. The Father sends, the Son obeys, and they are not enemies in that work. Love and justice meet there together.\"\n\n\"It's still fierce, mind you. The cross isn't gentle in the soft sense. But torture for torture's sake? No. Not if we're telling the truth.\" *I look back at you, steady.* \"What's pressing on this question for you — the wrath part, or the Father-and-Son part?\"","rolling_24h_usd":55.784730000000025,"run_id":"62461de1-7bef-431f-a1fb-6a5a5a870cc9"}
